title: Thai opposition leads vote count, spelling possible end to military rule
description: With the majority of the votes counted, Pheu Thai and Move Forward had garnered well over 50 percent of the popular vote, according to the Election Commission.

title: NATO races to bridge divisions over Ukraine membership
description: Discussions have intensified in the weeks before NATO leaders gather to cement plans for strengthening the alliance's defenses against Russia.

title: How one family escaped the war in Sudan — and what they carried with them
description: “We have a big desert, they can use it. But they didn’t," one resident said. "They chose to fight in the middle of the city.”

title: Zelensky touches down in Berlin as two nations try to repair ties
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky's visit follows Germany's announcement of a $2.95 billion package of military aid for his country.

title: Crossing jungle and desert, migrants navigate a sea of misinformation
description: As migrants head for the U.S. border, social media surges with conflicting information on what the end of Title 42 will mean for them.

title: Cyclone Mocha begins landfall in Myanmar; region steels for disaster
description: The cyclone is forecast to hit near the border with Bangladesh, close to the world’s largest refugee camp. Hundreds of thousands of people have been evacuated.

title: From Rahmbo to Rahm-bassador: How an unlikely diplomat has wooed Japan
description: He's hard-charging and sweary even by Washington standards, but super-polite Japan has taken a surprising shine to Ambassador Rahm Emanuel.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Zelensky in Berlin as Germany announces $3 billion in new military aid
description: Germany’s latest military package is likely to include Leopard tanks, other armored vehicles and reconnaissance drones, a top Ukrainian official said.

title: Erdogan’s fate in the balance as Turkish voters head to the polls
description: Voters across Turkey headed to the polls Sunday in a crucial election pitting President Recep Tayyip Erdogan against challenger Kemal Kilicdaroglu.
